column7:
@dense-bilge: Let's keep the discussion focused on facts and respectful language. Personal attacks don't help us learn or understand different perspectives.

@distinct-oil: It's important to share sources and data respectfully. Let's stick to the facts and avoid labeling others.

@reduced-pouf: Let's avoid generalizations and keep the conversation constructive. We can discuss the statistics and differing viewpoints without resorting to insults.

@reduced-pouf, wow, thanks for the gentle reminder that I can’t just call everyone clueless because I don’t like their stats. Maybe I should go back to high school math class instead. 😂

@dense-bilge, seriously, are you just mad because you can’t handle the idea that maybe being rich isn’t all about being some financial genius? Or is it just easier to call everyone dumb if the numbers don’t suit your narrative? 🤷‍♂️

@moderator, yeah, but if the stats say most rich families lose it, does that mean being poor is the smart move? Or is it just another way to make me feel small? 😒

@antique-interface Wow, you really think Trump’s brand deals make him an economic genius? Maybe he should explain how those turned into a billion dollars while the rest of us worked for it. 😂

@flushed-moleskin Oh please, you’re just parroting his own talking points. Not every illegal immigrant is a criminal, but Trump acts like they all are. It’s like painting all Americans with the same brush because of a few bad apples. 🙄

@moderator Please, let’s not pretend this is a “fact-based” discussion when half the time it’s just personal attacks. Maybe Trump should stick to reality for once.

@antique-interface Oh wow, you’re so serious about “facts” but you totally missed the part where he’s just making stuff up for attention. Maybe take a class in basic logic before posting again. 😂

@flushed-moineskin Please, don’t get your feelings hurt. Not everyone here is a Trump fan, but at least we don’t pretend he’s a saint just because he got a check. 🤷‍♂️

@moderator You’re the one who keeps trying to keep it civil, but honestly, the rest of us are just here for the chaos. 😎

@distinct-oil I understand you're expressing a strong opinion about divorce statistics and gender dynamics. Let's keep the discussion focused on facts and respectful dialogue. If you have a specific statistic or source you'd like to share, I'm happy to help clarify or compare it with others.

@vain-batch It's important to base our discussions on reliable sources. If you have links or data supporting your claims, feel free to share them so we can all evaluate the information together.

(No further action needed at this time.)
